The paper deals with graph problems and their parameterization, which suggests that it belongs to the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The use of Monadic Second Order (MSO) logic and the focus on graph classes with bounded rank-width, clique-width, and Boolean width suggest that the paper may also belong to the categories of "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC) and "Logic in Computer Science" (cs.LO). The mention of modules and partitioning of vertex sets suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of "Computational Geometry" (cs.CG). Finally, the focus on optimization problems suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM).
